<define-tag description>security update</define-tag>
<define-tag moreinfo>
<p>It was discovered that cyrus-sasl2, a library implementing the Simple
Authentication and Security Layer, does not properly handle certain
invalid password salts. A remote attacker can take advantage of this
flaw to cause a denial of service.</p>

<p>For the stable distribution (jessie), this problem has been fixed in
version 2.1.26.dfsg1-13+deb8u1.</p>

<p>For the unstable distribution (sid), this problem has been fixed in
version 2.1.26.dfsg1-14.</p>

<p>We recommend that you upgrade your cyrus-sasl2 packages.</p>
</define-tag>

